        <h2>Help and Support</h2> <!-- Section heading -->

        <!-- Getting Started Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Getting Started</h3>
            <p>Welcome to the Budget Claims System. This guide will help you navigate through the system and make the most of its features.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Login:</strong> Use your credentials to log in to the system. If you don't have an account, contact your administrator.</li>
                <li><strong>Dashboard:</strong> After logging in, you will be redirected to your dashboard, where you can see an overview of your activities and tasks.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Customer Functions Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Customer Functions</h3>
            <p>Customers can submit and view their claims through the customer portal.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Submit a Claim:</strong> Navigate to "Submit Claim" from the dashboard. Fill out the form with the required details including the MVA number and a description of the claim.</li>
                <li><strong>View Claims:</strong> To view submitted claims, go to "View Claims" from the dashboard. Here you can see the status and details of each claim.</li>
                <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Customers can update their account settings, change passwords, and manage 2FA from the "Settings" page.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Employee Functions Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Employee Functions</h3>
            <p>Employees can manage claims and perform administrative tasks through the employee portal.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Manage Claims:</strong> Employees can view, edit, and update claims. Go to "Manage Claims" to access the list of all claims.</li>
                <li><strong>Search Claims:</strong> Use the "Search Claims" feature to filter and find specific claims based on various criteria such as MVA, customer name, status, and date range.</li>
                <li><strong>Reports:</strong> Generate reports from the "Reports" page. You can export data in CSV, Excel, and PDF formats.</li>
                <li><strong>User Management:</strong> Admins and managers can manage user accounts by navigating to "User Management." Here, you can create, delete, and update user roles and permissions.</li>
                <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Employees can update their account settings, change passwords, and manage 2FA from the "Settings" page.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Two-Factor Authentication Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)</h3>
            <p>For added security, the Budget Claims System supports two-factor authentication.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Enable 2FA:</strong> Go to "Settings" and click "Enable 2FA." Follow the instructions to scan the QR code with your authenticator app and verify the token.</li>
                <li><strong>Disable 2FA:</strong> If you no longer want to use 2FA, go to "Settings" and click "Disable 2FA."</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Notifications Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Notifications</h3>
            <p>The system provides notifications for various events.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Email Notifications:</strong> You will receive email notifications for important events such as new claims, status updates, and reminders for pending tasks.</li>
                <li><strong>In-App Notifications:</strong> Notifications will also be displayed within the system for real-time updates.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Activity Logs Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Activity Logs</h3>
            <p>All user activities are logged for auditing purposes.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>View Logs:</strong> Admins can view activity logs to monitor user actions such as logins, claim submissions, edits, and deletions.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Email Templates Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Email Templates</h3>
            <p>When creating email templates, you can use the following variables to automatically fill in information from the claims:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>{MVA}: The Motor Vehicle Accident number.</li>
                <li>{CustomerName}: The name of the customer.</li>
                <li>{CustomerEmail}: The email of the customer.</li>
                <li>{CustomerNumber}: The phone number of the customer.</li>
                <li>{CustomerAddress}: The address of the customer.</li>
                <li>{CustomerDriversLicense}: The driver's license number of the customer.</li>
                <li>{CarMake}: The make of the car.</li>
                <li>{CarModel}: The model of the car.</li>
                <li>{CarYear}: The year of the car.</li>
                <li>{CarColor}: The color of the car.</li>
                <li>{CarVIN}: The Vehicle Identification Number of the car.</li>
                <li>{AccidentDate}: The date of the accident.</li>
                <li>{Billable}: Whether the claim is billable.</li>
                <li>{IsRenterAtFault}: Whether the renter is at fault.</li>
                <li>{DamagesTotal}: The total amount of damages.</li>
                <li>{BodyShopName}: The name of the body shop.</li>
                <li>{RANumber}: The RA number.</li>
                <li>{InsuranceCarrier}: The insurance carrier.</li>
                <li>{InsuranceAgent}: The insurance agent.</li>
                <li>{InsurancePhoneNumber}: The phone number of the insurance agent.</li>
                <li>{InsuranceFaxNumber}: The fax number of the insurance agent.</li>
                <li>{InsuranceAddress}: The address of the insurance agent.</li>
                <li>{InsuranceClaimNumber}: The insurance claim number.</li>
                <li>{ThirdPartyName}: The name of the third party.</li>
                <li>{ThirdPartyPhoneNumber}: The phone number of the third party.</li>
                <li>{ThirdPartyInsuranceName}: The name of the third party's insurance.</li>
                <li>{ThirdPartyPolicyNumber}: The policy number of the third party's insurance.</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Example Template</h4>
            <p><strong>Subject:</strong> Claim Update for {CustomerName}</p>
            <p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
            <pre>
Dear {CustomerName},

We wanted to provide you with an update on your claim regarding the accident on {AccidentDate}.

Details of your claim:
- MVA Number: {MVA}
- Customer Email: {CustomerEmail}
- Phone Number: {CustomerNumber}
- Address: {CustomerAddress}
- Car: {CarYear} {CarMake} {CarModel} ({CarColor})
- VIN: {CarVIN}

Insurance Information:
- Carrier: {InsuranceCarrier}
- Agent: {InsuranceAgent}
- Phone: {InsurancePhoneNumber}
- Fax: {InsuranceFaxNumber}
- Address: {InsuranceAddress}
- Claim Number: {InsuranceClaimNumber}

Third Party Information:
- Name: {ThirdPartyName}
- Phone: {ThirdPartyPhoneNumber}
- Insurance: {ThirdPartyInsuranceName}
- Policy Number: {ThirdPartyPolicyNumber}

Please let us know if you have any questions or need further assistance.

Best regards,
The Budget Claims System Team
            </pre>
        </section>

        <!-- Reports Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Reports</h3>
            <p>The system allows generating detailed reports for analysis.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Generate Reports:</strong> Go to the "Reports" section. Select the type of report, date range, and other criteria to generate the report.</li>
                <li><strong>Export Reports:</strong> Reports can be exported in various formats such as CSV, Excel, and PDF for further analysis.</li>
                <li><strong>Schedule Reports:</strong> You can schedule reports to be generated and emailed to specific recipients at regular intervals.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Audit Logs Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Audit Logs</h3>
            <p>The system maintains comprehensive logs of all activities for auditing purposes.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>View Audit Logs:</strong> Admins can access the audit logs from the "Audit Logs" section. Logs include details of actions performed by users such as logins, updates, and deletions.</li>
                <li><strong>Search Logs:</strong> Use the search functionality to filter logs based on user, action type, date range, etc.</li>
                <li><strong>Export Logs:</strong> Audit logs can be exported for external review or compliance purposes.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Data Backup and Recovery Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Data Backup and Recovery</h3>
            <p>The system provides options for data backup and recovery to ensure data integrity.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Backup Data:</strong> Regular backups are scheduled automatically. Admins can also initiate manual backups from the "Settings" page.</li>
                <li><strong>Restore Data:</strong> In case of data loss, admins can restore data from the backup files. Follow the instructions on the "Settings" page to perform a restore.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Import and Export Data Section -->
        <section>
            <h3>Import and Export Data</h3>
            <p>The Budget Claims System supports importing and exporting data for backup and restoration purposes.</p>
            <h4>Export Data</h4>
            <p>To export all data and associated files:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Navigate to <a href="/export/full">Export Data</a> or go to <code>http://localhost:5000/export/full</code>.</li>
                <li>This will generate a ZIP file containing:
                    <ul>
                        <li>All user data</li>
                        <li>All claims data</li>
                        <li>All associated files from the <code>uploads</code> directory</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Import Data</h4>
            <p>To import data from a previously exported ZIP file:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Navigate to <a href="/import">Import Data</a> or go to <code>http://localhost:5000/import</code>.</li>
                <li>Upload the ZIP file, and it will:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Insert users into the database</li>
                        <li>Insert claims into the database</li>
                        <li>Copy uploaded files to the <code>uploads</code> directory</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

